# RACV Salesforce Standards

SFDX monorepo `racv_ICT/salesforce2`. Metadata lives under
`force-app/main/default/**` and per-feature `packages/**`. Default branch is
`Develop`. AI output is a first draft — a human reviews and commits every change.

## Formatting

Follow `.prettierrc`: tabs, width 4, print width 120, double quotes, semicolons.
Don't reformat lines you didn't change.

## Naming

- Apex: PascalCase with the existing domain prefix (`LEI_`, `MEX_`, `APTS_`, `CB`);
  test class `<Name>Test`.
- LWC: camelCase folder and component.
- Custom Labels (LEI domain): `LEI_ClubMembership_<Feature>_<MsgType>`.

Match the surrounding files rather than introducing a new scheme.

## Engineering

- Read the sibling/related method before changing one; reuse the existing pattern
  instead of adding new SOQL/DML.
- Make the smallest change that solves the problem. Keep logic flat and readable —
  `||` over nested ternaries.
- Verify field and method API names against the metadata before using them (this
  org uses `Status__c`, not `Apttus_Config2__Status__c`).
- Ask when a requirement is ambiguous rather than guessing.

## Data handling

This is client production code.

- Never put real PII, payment data, secrets, tokens, or credentials in code,
  comments, prompts, or debug output — even temporarily.
- Sandbox data may contain real-looking PII; treat it the same.
- Don't send confidential logic or pricing to web search or external tools.

## Finishing a change

Before you stop, without being asked:

1. Self-review the diff against these standards and the Apex/LWC/test rules. List
   issues as `file:line — issue`, or state it's clean. Run `/review` for a full pass.
2. Propose a commit message `TSIP-XXXXX: <imperative summary>` (ticket from the
   branch name). Never run `git commit` or `git push` yourself.
